http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/Ransom-plan-flops-gang-of-kidnappers-held/article13975775.ece

Yelahanka New Town police have arrested a gang of four men, including an employee of an online marketing company, on the charge of kidnapping a 17-year-old student, Vydyanathan, who was later rescued by the police.The accused have been identified as Naveenkumar (22), a resident of Narayanapura, Ajith (21) of Vidyaranyapura, Edwin (24) of Vidyaranyapura, and Damodhar (20) of Tamil Nadu.According to the police, diploma graduates Naveenkumar and Ajith, while working as delivery boys for an online company, had been keeping a close tab on the family of the victim, Vydyanathan, who was one of their customers.BusinessWhen the two decided to launch a business venture, and needed Rs. 15 lakh as investment, they hit upon a plan to raise the money by asking for ransom after kidnapping Vydyanathan.On Monday morning, the student was on way to his college on his scooter along with his friend Nithish.The accused — Naveenkumar, Ajith, Edwin and Damodhar, travelling in a car — intercepted the students and attacked them.Vydyanathan was kidnapped. His friend, who was left behind near Harohalli lake, alerted the police.SearchA search was immediately launched, and Vydyanathan was found within five hours, tied up in a eucalyptus grove, on Hesaraghatta Road.Naveenkumar was arrested and the car hired by him was recovered.Based on information gathered during interrogation, the other three were also arrested, and a van and two two-wheelers were seized.A student, who was kidnapped on Monday morning, was rescued within five hoursThe student, who was kidnapped on Monday morning, was rescued within five hoursFour men have been arrested